(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Town Square
You stand in the Town Square of Thornwick, a modest trading town nestled between rolling hills and an ancient forest. The morning sun casts long shadows across the cobblestone plaza. A fountain splashes gently in the center, and pigeons peck at scattered breadcrumbs.

**Status:** Day $day | $time | Health: $health% | Gold: $gold gp | Reputation: $reputation

**Current Quest:** $mainQuest

---

Where will you venture?

[[→ Market Street]] — The bustling heart of commerce
[[→ North Gate]] — The forest awaits beyond
[[→ Back Alley]] — Dark secrets hidden away
[[→ Town Park]] — Nature's quiet refuge
[[→ Your House]] — The modest home you've rented
[[→ Rest at the fountain]] — Recover some health

---
{
  (if: $questLog's length > 0)[
    **Active Quests:**
    (for: each _q, ...$questLog)[
      • _q
    ]
  ]
}

:: Rest at the fountain
You sit by the fountain, letting the cool mist refresh you. The water feels rejuvenating.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 20))
(set: $time to "Mid-Morning")

(if: not $coinTaken)[
  As you rest, you notice something glinting beneath the water...
  
  [[Pick it up]] or [[Leave it be]] or [[Return to Town Square]]
]
(else)[
  You relax peacefully by the fountain.
  
  [[Return to Town Square]]
]

:: Pick it up
You reach into the fountain and retrieve a tarnished silver coin. It feels warm to the touch.

(set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Ancient Silver Coin"))
(set: $gold to $gold + 5)
(set: $coinTaken to true)

*You've obtained: Ancient Silver Coin and gained 5 gold!*

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Leave it be
You decide the coin is best left undisturbed.

(set: $coinTaken to true)

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Return to Town Square
(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Market Street
The vibrant energy of Market Street engulfs you. Merchants line the cobbled street, shouting their wares. Colorful flags flutter overhead. The aroma of fresh bread, spiced leather, and exotic spices fills your senses.

**Locations:**
• [[Bakery]] — Warmth and fresh bread
• [[General Shop]] — Tools and mysterious trinkets
• [[Suspicious Man]] — A hooded figure watching the crowd
• [[Food Stall]] — Quick meals
• [[Return to Town Square]]

---

(set: $time to "Midday")

:: Bakery
You push open the wooden door. A warm gust of air carries the smell of fresh bread. The baker, a woman named **Elara**, smiles warmly from behind the counter.

**Elara says:** "Welcome, wanderer. You look new to our town. Can I help you?"

(if: not $bakerMet)[
  (set: $bakerMet to true)
  (set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)
  (unless: "Learn more about the forest and its mysteries" is in $questLog)[
    (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Learn more about the forest and its mysteries"))
  ]
]

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Talk about the town
"Thornwick is a good place," Elara muses, kneading dough. "Most folks are honest. We get travelers, merchants, adventurers. The guard keeps us safe, though there's been talk of strange happenings in the forest lately."

She leans in conspiratorially. "The old man in the park—**Thorne**—might know more than he lets on. And that suspicious fellow near the square? Never quite trusted him."

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Ask about the forest
Elara's expression darkens. "The forest wasn't always dangerous. But something changed five years ago. Travelers stopped coming from that direction. Strange lights appear some nights."

She glances out nervously. "If you're thinking of going in there, be careful. Take supplies."

(unless: $forestUnlocked)[
  (set: $forestUnlocked to true)
]

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Buy a bread roll (5 gp)]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Buy a bread roll (5 gp)
(if: $gold >= 5)[
  (if: not ("Fresh Bread Roll" is in $inventory))[
    (set: $gold to $gold - 5)
    (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Fresh Bread Roll"))
  ]
  (set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 15))
  *You've purchased a fresh bread roll. Delicious!*
]
(else)[
  "I'm sorry, friend," Elara says gently. "That'll cost you 5 gold, and you don't have enough."
]

[[Talk about the town]]
[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Leave the Bakery]]

:: Leave the Bakery
You thank Elara and step back out into Market Street.

[[Market Street]]

:: General Shop
The shop is cramped and cluttered. Shelves overflow with mysterious items. The shopkeeper, **Garrett**, sits behind the counter, polishing an ornate dagger.

He looks up from his work. "Need something? I've got rare finds."

**Garrett's Inventory:**
• Rope Coil (10 gp) — Useful for climbing
• Mysterious Map (25 gp) — Shows an "X" in the forest
• Healing Potion (15 gp) — Restores 30% health
• Lantern (20 gp) — Essential for dark places

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Buy Rope Coil (10 gp)]]
[[Buy Mysterious Map (25 gp)]]
[[Buy Healing Potion (15 gp)]]
[[Buy Lantern (20 gp)]]
[[Leave the General Shop]]

:: Ask about the forest
Garrett's weathered face becomes grave. "That forest... it's changed, friend. Five years ago, something happened. A curse, or perhaps something darker."

He slides a worn journal across the counter. "Found this in a crashed wagon. The explorer who wrote it was heading into the forest. Never came back."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Buy Rope Coil (10 gp)]]
[[Buy Mysterious Map (25 gp)]]
[[Buy Healing Potion (15 gp)]]
[[Buy Lantern (20 gp)]]
[[Leave the General Shop]]

