(if: $gold >= 4)[
  (set: $gold to $gold - 4)
  (set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 5))
  "Delicious!"
]
(else)[
  "You're a bit short on coin."
]

[[Buy Hearty Soup (8 gp)]]
[[Buy Roasted Vegetables (6 gp)]]
[[Return to Market Street]]

:: Return to Market Street
(go-to: "Market Street")

:: North Gate
The North Gate stands imposing and ancient. Beyond it, the forest looms like a living wall—trees so tall they seem to touch the sky, their canopy so thick that even midday light struggles to penetrate.

A grizzled guard in armor stands at attention. His name is **Aldric**, and his weathered face speaks of decades of service.

"Halt," he says, not unkindly. "You look like you're thinking about heading into those woods."

(if: not $guardWarned)[
  (set: $guardWarned to true)
  (set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)
]

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Ask why it's dangerous]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask about the forest
Aldric takes a long breath. "The forest wasn't always like this. Five years ago, something changed. An old expedition went in, led by a scholar named **Marcus**. He was looking for ancient ruins. His team never returned."

He gazes into the darkness. "After that, the forest became... hostile. We've sent patrols, but they all come back traumatized."

(unless: "Discover what happened to Marcus and his expedition" is in $questLog)[
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover what happened to Marcus and his expedition"))
]

[[Ask why it's dangerous]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask why it's dangerous
"Beasts," Aldric says flatly. "Not like normal creatures. These things have intelligence and malevolence. We've lost good soldiers."

He looks at you seriously. "The forest has a guardian, or perhaps a curse. Anyone who goes in unprepared doesn't come out."

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Ask if there's a way in]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask if there's a way in
"There is one path," Aldric admits reluctantly. "The old forest road. It's overgrown now, but if you follow the stone markers—ancient things carved with symbols—you can find your way deeper in."

He points toward the forest. "Follow the silver stones. They'll take you to the old observation tower."

(unless: "Find the old forest road marked with silver stones" is in $questLog)[
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Find the old forest road marked with silver stones"))
]

[[Ask about the forest]]
[[Try to convince him to let you pass]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Try to convince him to let you pass
Aldric watches you for a long moment. "You're brave, I'll give you that. Or foolish. Most likely both."

He steps aside slightly. "I can't stop you—the gates aren't locked. But hear this: the forest will test you. Stay true to your purpose, and you might survive."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

[[Enter the forest]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Enter the forest
You push open the heavy gates. The forest looms before you, vast and primordial. The air grows cold as shadows engulf you.

(set: $time to "Afternoon")

[[The Ancient Forest Path]]

:: The Ancient Forest Path
You step into the forest. Immediately, the sounds of the town fade. The trees are impossibly old, their bark thick and gnarled. Moss and fungus cover rotting logs.

You notice the forest road—barely visible beneath centuries of overgrowth—and the first silver stone, carved with mysterious symbols.

As you walk, you hear sounds. Whispers on the wind. Unseen footsteps. The distant cry of something large.

The forest is testing you.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]] — The safe path
[[Venture off the path]] — The mysterious route
[[Return to town]] — Safety awaits

:: Follow the silver stone markers
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 10))

You follow the silver stones, each one leading deeper. After hours of walking, you discover something extraordinary—the old observation tower, covered in vines and crumbling with age. Behind it stands an ancient archway of stone.

**You've found the Gateway to the Old Ruins.**

[[Investigate the archway]]
[[Rest at the tower]]
[[Return to town]]

:: Investigate the archway
You approach the archway cautiously. It's carved with the same symbols as the silver stones, but far more intricate. In the center, there's a lock with no visible keyhole.

Suddenly, you remember the Ancient Silver Coin you found in the fountain. You pull it out, and it glows with the same light as the stones.

(if: "Ancient Silver Coin" is in $inventory)[
  The coin slides perfectly into a hidden slot. The stone glows brilliantly, and with a deep rumble, the archway opens, revealing a passage into the earth below.
  
  **You've unlocked the passage to the Ancient Library!**
  
  (unless: "Explore the Ancient Library" is in $questLog)[
    (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Explore the Ancient Library"))
  ]
  (unless: "Opened the Gateway to the Old Ruins" is in $completedQuests)[
    (set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Opened the Gateway to the Old Ruins"))
  ]
  
  [[Enter the Library]]
]
(else)[
  Without the key, the archway remains sealed. You'll need to find something to unlock it.
  
  [[Rest at the tower]]
  [[Return to town]]
]

:: Enter the Library
(set: $time to "Evening")
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 10))

You descend into darkness. Your footsteps echo on ancient stone. The air grows warmer, and a faint blue light emanates from within.

You emerge into a vast underground chamber. Books line endless shelves. At the center stands a stone pedestal with a scroll of incredible age. Behind it, you see a skeleton—the remains of **Marcus**, the missing scholar.

Next to the skeleton is a journal filled with frantic notes about "the curse," "the stone's power," and "the ritual that went wrong."

[[Read Marcus's Journal]]
[[Take the ancient scroll]]
[[Pay respects and leave]]

:: Read Marcus's Journal
You carefully open the journal. The entries tell a tragic story:

*"Day 1: We've found the library!"*
*"Day 7: We've found an ancient stone of immense power."*
*"Day 12: Something went wrong. The forest itself has awakened."*
*"Day 15: I'm the only one left. I can't leave. This journal is my legacy."*

(if: not ("Marcus's Journal" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Marcus's Journal"))
]

(unless: "Discover the truth about the curse" is in $questLog)[
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover the truth about the curse"))
]

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 3)

[[Take the ancient scroll]]
[[Pay respects and leave]]

:: Take the ancient scroll
You carefully lift the scroll from the pedestal. It's warm to the touch, and ancient symbols glow softly on its surface. The scroll describes an ancient ritual—a way to bind the curse and restore the forest to peace.

(if: not ("Scroll of Unbinding" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Scroll of Unbinding"))
  (set: $treasureItemObtained to true)
]

(unless: "Perform the Unbinding Ritual to free the forest" is in $questLog)[
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Perform the Unbinding Ritual to free the forest"))
]

(unless: "Discovered the truth in the Ancient Library" is in $completedQuests)[
  (set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Discovered the truth in the Ancient Library"))
]

[[Perform the ritual here]]
[[Return to town with the knowledge]]

:: Perform the ritual here
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 20))

You unfurl the scroll and begin to read the ancient words aloud. Your voice echoes through the chamber. The stone beneath your feet begins to glow, brighter and brighter.

Reality seems to shimmer. The curse unravels. When the light fades, silence returns.

**The curse is broken. The forest is free.**

(unless: "Performed the Unbinding Ritual" is in $completedQuests)[
  (set: $completedQuests to $completedQuests + (a: "Performed the Unbinding Ritual"))
]

(set: $questLog to $questLog - (a: "Perform the Unbinding Ritual to free the forest"))
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 10)

You've become a hero.

[[Return to town]]

:: Return to town with the knowledge
The forest path seems easier now, as if it's guiding you back. The ancient corruption feels diminished.

You emerge from the forest as dusk falls, carrying knowledge that could save your town.

(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Pay respects and leave
You bow respectfully before Marcus's remains, grateful for his sacrifice.

(if: not ("Marcus's Journal" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Marcus's Journal"))
]

[[Return to town]]

:: Return to town
(go-to: "Town Square")

:: Rest at the tower
You make camp at the tower, gathering your strength for what comes next.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 30))
(set: $time to "Night")

In the morning, you'll decide what to do.

[[Investigate the archway]]
[[Return to town]]

:: Venture off the path
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 20))

You leave the marked path, following your instincts deeper. The trees close in. You hear whispers and see shapes moving in the darkness.

After what feels like hours, you stumble into a clearing where a massive stone statue stands. At its base, you find something glinting: a key made of crystal.

[[Take the key]]
[[Leave the clearing and find the path]]

:: Take the key
(if: not ("Crystal Key" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Crystal Key"))
  (set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)
  
  The moment you touch it, you understand—this key belongs to something ancient.
]
(else)[
  You already have the crystal key.
]

[[Find the path back]]

:: Find the path back
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 10))

You manage to find your way back to the silver stone markers.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]]

:: Leave the clearing and find the path
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 5))

You carefully back away from the statue and find your way back to the silver stones.

[[Follow the silver stone markers]]

:: Back Alley
The alley is narrow and dark, squeezed between two old buildings. Water drips from a broken gutter. A door, painted deep green, stands slightly ajar.

[[Investigate the sound]]
[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Search the trash]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Investigate the sound
(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

You follow the dripping sound to a broken pipe. Behind it, you notice a small leather pouch containing 15 gold and a note:

*"For whoever finds this. I'm sorry for what I've done. The curse in the forest... I helped cause it. Forgive me. —M"*

(if: not $noteFound)[
  (if: not ("Mysterious Note" is in $inventory))[
    (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Mysterious Note"))
  ]
  (set: $gold to $gold + 15)
  (set: $noteFound to true)
  
  (unless: "Discover who left this note and what they meant" is in $questLog)[
    (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Discover who left this note and what they meant"))
  ]
]
(else)[
  You've already collected this note.
]

[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Search the trash]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Knock on the green door
The door opens wider, revealing a dimly lit room filled with curiosities. Behind a cluttered desk sits an elderly woman with sharp eyes.

"Come in, come in," she says. "I've been expecting someone."

She introduces herself as **Iris**, a hedge witch and keeper of forgotten knowledge.

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)

[[Ask what she knows about the forest]]
[[Ask what she is]]
[[Leave]]

:: Ask what she knows about the forest
"The forest is cursed by ambition and greed," Iris says solemnly. "A scholar tried to use ancient power. The forest punished him for it. But the curse can be broken."

She slides a small vial across her desk. "This potion will help you see the truth in the forest."

(if: not $irisQuestAccepted)[
  (if: not ("Iris's Truth Potion" is in $inventory))[
    (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Iris's Truth Potion"))
  ]
  (set: $irisQuestAccepted to true)
  
  (unless: "Use Iris's potion to see the truth in the forest" is in $questLog)[
    (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Use Iris's potion to see the truth in the forest"))
  ]
]
(else)[
  "I hope my potion has helped you see clearly," Iris says mysteriously.
]

[[Ask what she is]]
[[Leave]]

:: Ask what she is
"I am someone who remembers," Iris says mysteriously. "I remember when the forest was beautiful. I've been waiting for someone brave enough to undo what was done."

(set: $reputation to $reputation + 1)

[[Ask what she knows about the forest]]
[[Leave]]

:: Leave
You step back out into the alley.

[[Back Alley]]

:: Search the trash
(set: $health to (max: 0, $health - 5))

You search through refuse and garbage. In an old crate, you discover a rusted key and a broken compass.

(if: not ("Rusted Key" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Rusted Key"))
]
(if: not ("Broken Compass" is in $inventory))[
  (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Broken Compass"))
]

[[Knock on the green door]]
[[Investigate the sound]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Town Park
The park is a sanctuary of peace. Ancient oaks provide shade, and benches line the walking paths. A small pond reflects the sky, and wildflowers bloom in carefully tended gardens.

Sitting on a weathered bench, watching the water, is an elderly man. His eyes seem to contain centuries of wisdom.

[[Sit on the bench]]
[[Talk to the old man]]
[[Explore the park]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Sit on the bench
You sit down quietly, letting the peace of the park wash over you.

(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 15))

After a while, the old man speaks. "It's a good place for thinking, isn't it?"

[[Talk to the old man]]

:: Talk to the old man
The old man introduces himself as **Thorne**, and he claims to be over a hundred years old. His mind is sharp.

"I remember when the forest was young," he says. "When it was beautiful and safe. I think something in its heart has been corrupted, and I think you might be the one to fix it."

(if: not $oldManMet)[
  (set: $oldManMet to true)
  (set: $reputation to $reputation + 2)
  
  (if: not ("Thorne's Token" is in $inventory))[
    (set: $inventory to $inventory + (a: "Thorne's Token"))
  ]
]

[[Ask about the forest's history]]
[[Ask how he knows about you]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask about the forest's history
"Five hundred years ago," Thorne begins, "the forest was a paradise. Then came the ambition of men. Scholars and mages tried to unlock its secrets. They found an ancient artifact of great power."

He pauses, lost in memory. "The forest rejected them. It awakened defenses. But the corruption spread, year by year, until five years ago, when a new attempt was made."

[[Ask how he knows about you]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Ask how he knows about you
Thorne smiles. "I know because I've lived long enough to recognize the signs. When someone new arrives in town, I can feel it. When that someone carries the weight of destiny, I can see it in their eyes. You're here for a reason."

[[Ask about the forest's history]]
[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Explore the park
You wander through the park's quiet paths, finding small surprises—a hidden fountain, a grove of ancient trees, a stone monument covered in names.

The names are those of people lost to the forest over centuries.

(unless: "Understand why so many have been lost to the forest" is in $questLog)[
  (set: $questLog to $questLog + (a: "Understand why so many have been lost to the forest"))
]

[[Return to Town Square]]

:: Your House
Your small rented home is modest but comfortable. A window overlooks the town.

(set: $houseExplored to true)

What will you do here?

[[Look out the window]]
[[Rest on the bed]]
[[Examine your belongings]]
[[Leave]]

:: Look out the window
You gaze out over the town of Thornwick, watching the sunset. From here, you can see the market, the north gate, and in the distance, the dark mass of the forest.

[[Rest on the bed]]
[[Leave]]

:: Rest on the bed
(set: $health to (min: 100, $health + 25))
(set: $time to "Morning")
(set: $day to $day + 1)

You sleep deeply and wake refreshed. A new day awaits.

[[Look out the window]]
[[Leave]]

